      "properties": {
        "content": "What the PROS don't want YOU \ud83e\udef5 to know part #26\n\nThe REAL Secrets of optimizing your monitor (NEVER SEEN BEFORE)\n\n1. Open nvidia control panel, go to change resolution, select customize.\n\n2. Enable resolutions not exposed by display & click create custom resolution.\n\n3. Set desired resolution & set timing to manual instead of automatic.\n\n4. Decrease both Front Porch & Sync Width on both sides using the test button until you notice display glitching/out of range/not turning on. Click no if your screen is visibly fine and continue dialing them in. Then once you've dialed in the front porch and sync widths to the lowest number, you're going to increase the Vertical Total at the bottom right to the highest value you can. I would recommend doing it by 25-50 increases in the number.\n\nMisc: When you use the test button in the nvidia control panel it resets the setting you applied using the test button in 15 seconds if you dont click yes. Sometimes it can bug out & you have to switch your GPU hdmi/display port to get it back. You can mess with the polarities but I use positive/negative. This wont damage anything, it's safe to do.\n\nIf you want more real secrets like this you have to show me you care by following, dropping a comment, or at least liking my tweets. All i ask is a little respect <3\n\n(disc below for help/services/etc)",
